name: Counting on fingers
curriculargoal: CG-8: Children develop mathematical understanding and abilities to recognize the world through quantities, shapes, and measures
competencies: {C-8.3: Counts up to 99 both forwards and backwards and in groups of 10s and 20s Counts up to 99 both forwards and backwards and in groups of 10s and 20s}
learningoutcomes:
Says/sings number names verbally till 5 in correct sequence/orde r with context
Imitates adults while counting using one to one correspondenc e between number names and objects till 3
Counts objects up to 3 and develop understanding of cardinality till 3 (e.g., counts 3 things in a set and says those are 3)
Counts given manipulatives or objects and can pick and give up to 5 things
Compares quantities between two sets and can distinguish if they are the same or more up to 3 objects
Recognizes instantly the count of a collection of 2 or 3 objects

name: Backward counting 20 to 0
curriculargoal: CG-8: Children develop mathematical understanding and abilities to recognize the world through quantities, shapes, and measures
competencies: {C-8.3: Counts up to 99 both forwards and backwards and in groups of 10s and 20s Counts up to 99 both forwards and backwards and in groups of 10s and 20s}
learningoutcomes:
Says/sings number names in correct sequence up to 20 and keeps one to one correspondence with counting words and counting objects till 10.
Counts objects with understanding of cardinality till 10 accurately
Counts objects in any order accurately in a given set and understands that the quantity remains same irrespective of the order in which the objects are being counted, (e.g., given a handful of beads, children can count in any order and be able to tell the quantity accurately)
Understands the concept of 0 as a number by reducing (backward counting) objects in a set (e.g., backward counting of 3 beads, after 1 what is left?)
Demonstrates the understanding of the numeral as face value and positioning value (ordinality). And ordinal position of an object from left to right vice versa.
Recognizes instantly the count of a collection of 6 objects (e.g., recognize 6 biscuits, chocolates, or blocks without counting)

Counts forward and backward from a specific number (between 0 and 99)

Recognizes quantities in groups of 2 (e.g., two groups of ten makes 20)
